(1) One or more of the following punishments may be imposed by any appropriate tribunal upon a defaulter who has pleaded guilty or who has been found guilty of an offence against discipline: (a) reduction in rank; (b) confinement in a guardroom, or restriction to the confines of any camp or other area where a part of the Service is stationed, for not more than fourteen days; (c) a fine not exceeding thirty penalty units; (d) stoppage of allowance; (e) extra drills or parades; (f) dismissal from the Service .
